It's understood students are unhappy over their NSFAS allowance for food and books and have vowed to continue with the shutdown until their demands are met. JOHANNESBURG - Management at the University of Venda says it sympathises with its striking students, while the institution remains closed. It's understood students are unhappy over their National Student Financial Aid Scheme (NSFAS) allowance for food and books and have vowed to continue with the shutdown until their demands are met. The university has been closed for a week.University spokesperson Takalani Dzaga says the university's management met with students this week to discuss a way forward. During the meeting students agreed to call of the strike but they said they will not be going back to class until such time all the payments have been made. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)